31/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Hungarian President Ferenc Madl confirmed on Wednesday (30 March) his country's support for Albania's bid to join Euro-Atlantic structures.
During talks with Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu in Tirana, Madl said Hungary is ready to assist Albania in implementing reforms related to EU and NATO accession.
He added that Hungarian investors are eyeing the Albanian market, particularly the privatisation process and tourism.
(Albanian News - 31/03/05;
Albanian government Web site - 30/03/05)
